HEADWORD: Onocerin
<hw>On`o*ce"rin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.
<ets>Ononis</ets>, the generic name of the plant + L. <ets>cera</ets>
wax.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A white crystalline waxy substance
extracted from the root of the leguminous plant <spn>Ononis
spinosa</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

